50|$|Class C {{airspace}} {{is defined}} below 8100 m and allows IFR and VFR operations. Both IFR and VFR operations {{are required to}} have permanent two-way radio contact with ATC. IFR flights are separated {{from each other and}} from <b>VFR</b> <b>flights.</b> <b>VFR</b> <b>flights</b> are separated from IFR flights and are provided traffic information about other <b>VFR</b> <b>flights.</b> Permission for using airspace is required except for the special cases listed in clause 114 of the Federal rules for using Russian air space.|$|E
50|$|The ICAO {{definition}} of Special <b>VFR</b> <b>flight</b> is a <b>VFR</b> <b>flight</b> cleared by {{air traffic control}} to operate within a control zone in meteorological conditions below visual meteorological conditions.|$|R
